-- Celpa Bonds Plunge After Company Files for Bankruptcy Protection
-- B y   B o r i s   K o r b y
-- 2012-02-28T21:09:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/celpa-bonds-plunge-after-company-files-for-bankruptcy-protection.html
Bonds issued by Centrais Eletricas
do Para SA, known as Celpa, tumbled after the company filed for
 bankruptcy protection . The securities dropped 29 cents to 75
cents on the dollar as of 4:04 p.m. in  New York , according to
Trace, the bond price reporting system of the Financial Industry
Regulatory Authority.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Boris Korby in New York at 
 bkorby1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  